race.comment: ROCKBARTON ANGEL (11) ran the in-form Oui Oui Oui to 1.1 lengths when resuming two runs ago then got a long way back last start over 1350m at the Beaumont track and failed to feature. Has won two from two over this distance including a barnstorming victory at this stage last prep at Newcastle. Primed to take this out. TACT (2) has settled midfield but failed to make much impression in his two runs this prep, both over shorter trips at the provincials. Strips fitter and is back a little in grade so watch for a far better performance. NAUGHTY NURSE (9) scored a big win here at this distance two runs back then failed to flatter subsequently at Wyong. Loves this circuit and can bounce back. PHOENIX POWER (7) had a 32-day reset and ran a much better race at his latest outing over 1450m at Kempsey. Not sure he can win but is a worthwhile exotics inclusion. ANNULUS (3) wasn't beaten far first-up at Taree after giving away a big start. In the mix over this more suitable trip.
